---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Botswana Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/botswana/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Namibia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/namibia' },
  { title: 'Zimbabwe for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/zimbabwe' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'botswanaFit', header: 'Botswana Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BWP$5,900-8,425/mo', botswanaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BWP$6,900-9,850/mo', botswanaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BWP$5,310-7,580/mo', botswanaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BWP$4,930-7,040/mo', botswanaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (BPOMAS, MRI)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'BWP$1,500-3,500/mo', botswanaFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BWP$5,310-8,425', annual: 'BWP$63,720-101,100' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BWP$7,280-11,230', annual: 'BWP$87,360-134,760' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BWP$9,800-15,085', annual: 'BWP$117,600-181,020' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'BWP$300-800/visit', annual: 'Moderate' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'BWP$2,000-5,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Botswana 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Botswana. Safari paradise, stable democracy, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Botswana"
  subheadline="Botswana offers Africa's most stable democracy, stunning Okavango Delta wildlife, English as official language, and good governance—premier safari destination for adventurous retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/botswana-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Botswana</h2>
  <p>
    Botswana offers Africa's longest continuous democracy, stunning Okavango Delta (UNESCO), excellent wildlife, English as official language, and diamond-funded prosperity. For adventurous retirees seeking premier African safari lifestyle with stability, Botswana delivers exceptional experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Gaborone is the capital with best healthcare. Maun is gateway to Okavango Delta. Kasane provides access to Chobe National Park. Francistown is commercial hub. Most expats choose Gaborone for healthcare; safari regions for lifestyle despite healthcare limitations.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good for Africa; South Africa backup common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (official); Setswana widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BWP$10,000-20,000/month (~$740-1,480 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Semi-arid; hot summers; mild dry winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Stable; democratic; wildlife-focused</li>
      <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> 1-hour flight to Johannesburg</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Botswana Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Botswana healthcare is good for Africa—Gaborone Private Hospital and Bokamoso Private Hospital provide modern care. Government has invested diamond revenues in healthcare. However, complex cases often need South Africa evacuation. Johannesburg is 1-hour flight with world-class facilities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Safari areas have limited healthcare—clinic level at best. Evacuation to Gaborone or South Africa essential. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage non-negotiable for safari regions. Medical tourism to South Africa common for specialists.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">South Africa Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      South Africa provides world-class medical backup—Johannesburg is 1-hour flight with excellent hospitals. Include South Africa in insurance coverage. Gaborone handles routine care; Johannesburg provides complex treatment. Safari areas require evacuation capability.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Botswana has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for many nationalities including US, UK, Commonwealth. Good for exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Extension</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available beyond 90 days. Apply through immigration department.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories including retirement. Requires proof of income and clean record.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For employment. Some semi-retired professionals use this route with tourism businesses.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Botswana:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> No insurance required for short stays</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> South Africa coverage essential</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Botswana</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with South Africa evacuation coverage essential. Gaborone private hospitals handle routine care. Johannesburg provides world-class backup for complex conditions. Safari regions require robust evacuation. Don't economize on coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Botswana, South Africa evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Botswana</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Africa network, excellent evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> World-class healthcare 1 hour away</li>
    <li><strong>Safari regions:</strong> Evacuation coverage essential</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with strong Africa evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Botswana (BWP ~13.5 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Gaborone base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa network:</strong> Use designated hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Use for local routine care</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Southern Africa focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Safari Lodge Owner, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $5,000/month income. Business permit. Maun area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global premium with maximum evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BWP$7,000/month (~$520). Remote location; Johannesburg backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: South African Neighbor, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> ZAR$45,000/month pension. Residence permit. Gaborone.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with South Africa home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BWP$8,500/month (~$630). Border ease; home backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Wildlife Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £3,500/month pension. Residence permit. Kasane.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with strong evacuation to Johannesburg.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BWP$6,500/month (~$480). Chobe access; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Botswana really that stable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Africa's longest continuous democracy since independence (1966). Peaceful transitions of power. Low corruption for Africa. Diamond wealth well-managed. Strong institutions. Often called "Africa's success story" for governance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English sufficient?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—English is official language. Government, business, healthcare all operate in English. Setswana widely spoken locally but English is universal. No language barrier for English speakers. Former British protectorate influence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's healthcare like in safari areas?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very limited—basic clinics at best. Most lodges have first aid and evacuation protocols. Air evacuation to Gaborone or Johannesburg standard for serious conditions. Robust insurance with evacuation coverage non-negotiable for safari regions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is it expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—more expensive than some African countries. Diamond wealth means prices higher than neighbors. Safari tourism premium pricing. Gaborone reasonable. Import costs add to prices. Budget $1,000-2,000/month for comfortable life.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Botswana coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Botswana authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
